.TH SHOREWALL-NFT-TCDEVICES 5 "2026-04-20" "shorewall-nft 1.10.0" "File Formats"
.SH NAME
shorewall\-nft\-tcdevices \- traffic shaping device declarations for shorewall-nft
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.I tcdevices
file declares the interfaces used for traffic shaping.  shorewall-nft does
not emit nft rules for traffic shaping directly; instead it can either
apply the configuration directly via
.B shorewall\-nft apply\-tc
(preferred — uses pyroute2, no tc(8) binary required) or generate a
.BR tc (8)
shell script via
.B shorewall\-nft generate\-tc
(portable fallback).  Both commands use the qdiscs and classes declared
in this file together with
.I tcclasses
and
.IR tcfilters .

.SH FILE FORMAT
Location:
.I /etc/shorewall/tcdevices
(or inside a merged
.IR /etc/shorewall46/ ).
.PP
Columns are whitespace-separated.  Lines beginning with
.B #
are comments.

.TS
l l l.
Column	Required	Description
_
INTERFACE	yes	Interface name
IN_BANDWIDTH	yes	Ingress bandwidth (e.g. 100mbit)
OUT_BANDWIDTH	yes	Egress bandwidth (e.g. 100mbit)
OPTIONS	no	Comma-separated options (classify, …)
REDIRECT	no	Redirect device for ingress shaping
.TE

Bandwidth values use tc notation:
.BR kbit ,
.BR mbit ,
.BR gbit .

.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Declare a 100 Mbit uplink with a known egress rate:
.RS
.nf
#INTERFACE  IN_BANDWIDTH  OUT_BANDWIDTH
eth0        100mbit       10mbit
.fi
.RE
.PP
Asymmetric ADSL-style link:
.RS
.nf
eth0        8mbit         768kbit
.fi
.RE

.SH SEE ALSO
.BR shorewall\-nft (8),
.BR shorewall\-nft\-tcclasses (5),
.BR shorewall\-nft\-tcfilters (5),
.BR tc (8)

